Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:02:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,(gasping for breath)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.78,0:02:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,(eerie music)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.23,0:02:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,(footsteps)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.73,0:02:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Gods, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.69,0:02:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,(gasps)\N(basket hitting ground)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.23,0:03:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ruby] We need to\Ntake the relic to Atlas?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.90,0:03:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's what Oz said.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- You've got to be joking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.57,0:03:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Nora] I mean bright side
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we finally get out of this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.61,0:03:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well trust me, I'm not\Ncrazy about it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.23,0:03:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And without the Spring\NMaiden here to seal the relic
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,back in its vault, it's our best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- Atlas may be the safest\Nkingdom we have at the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.03,0:03:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but their borders are closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.44,0:03:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,General Ironwood called everyone back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Eh, not everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The city of Argus is a ways north of us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.82,0:03:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the primary trading\Nport between Anima and Solitas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.69,0:03:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got the largest Atlas
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.11,0:03:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,military base outside of the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.61,0:03:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way they'd leave it abandoned
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.61,0:03:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we play our cards right
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there's a good chance\Nwe could convince them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to escort us straight to Ironwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.03,0:04:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- I mean we do have the missing Heiress
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.48,0:04:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Schnee Dust Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.15,0:04:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ex-heiress actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.11,0:04:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- True, true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.73,0:04:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there's a chance of\Nreward money I say we go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.44,0:04:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,(frustrated sigh)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] Hopefully the\Nfirst option will suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.82,0:04:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- Glad to see you're feeling better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Likewise, and while\NI'm sure we could all use
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.40,0:04:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,more time to recover, I'm\Nafraid time is of the essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.03,0:04:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right, as long as that\Nthing's out in the open
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.82,0:04:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,its power could fall\Ninto the wrong hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.69,0:04:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Speaking of, what does it do exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.19,0:04:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Qrow never really told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.86,0:04:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.86,0:04:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The relic of knowledge has a wonderful,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and incredibly dangerous ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.78,0:04:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Its user can ask any question,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:04:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lamp will provide an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.90,0:05:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Indeed, however it's\Nnot without drawbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The lamp cannot tell you of events\Nthat have yet to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will only ever\Nanswer three questions...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.19,0:05:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,every 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.32,0:05:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, I guess that's not so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.73,0:05:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Adds a lot of pressure though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Then let's put it to a vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.11,0:05:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we ask first?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.19,0:05:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we ask for more questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.36,0:05:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we ask for more questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.98,0:05:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're not wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- (chuckles) I'm afraid\Nyou won't be able to ask
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.23,0:05:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it anything at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.11,0:05:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The questions were used\Nbefore I sealed it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.28,0:05:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, at least now we know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll be sure to keep it safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.07,0:05:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- Great, this is just great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:05:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We're stranded.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.69,0:06:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We lost a third of our party.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.65,0:06:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have gained a defenseless old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- My name is Maria Calavera,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.15,0:06:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am not defenseless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.69,0:06:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just a little hard of hearing\Nand blind without my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.65,0:06:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That are in desperate need of repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.86,0:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm starting to see your point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yang, knock it off, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lose our cool now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll just be inviting even more Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- Does that even matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.73,0:06:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently we've been attracting\NGrimm since we left Haven.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh and how could I forget about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to no more\Nlies and half-truths?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.61,0:06:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, I think it's time\Nwe got an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.90,0:06:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.69,0:06:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well you certainly didn't tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,everything about the relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, now is not the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.11,0:06:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, we're past that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.40,0:06:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna know why you're still\Nnot telling us everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.65,0:07:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- It is true that the Grimm\Nare attracted to the relics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.69,0:07:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's faint, but undeniable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it has to do with their origin,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.23,0:07:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm not entirely sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.82,0:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless, I feared\Nthat making you all aware
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,would only add anxiety and negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.94,0:07:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed like the safer option.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.40,0:07:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know, I'm getting real tired
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.69,0:07:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of people choosing what's best for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Is that why you chose to lie to everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.98,0:07:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about Lionheart too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.61,0:07:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, as a matter of fact, I believed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Kingdom of Mistral\Ndeserved better than the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.90,0:07:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I believed Leonardo\Ndeserved to be remembered
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.98,0:07:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for his lifetime of service,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.73,0:07:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the unfortunate missteps he made
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.57,0:07:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in his final years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.61,0:07:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Missteps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.61,0:07:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- What professor Lionheart\Ndid was reprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.11,0:07:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not here to argue differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but does one lapse in\Njudgment truly negate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.28,0:07:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all of his good?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.53,0:07:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we not all have regrets?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have met Professor Lionheart,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but you never met the man he\Nwas before Salem found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look we're supposed\Nto be in this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.73,0:07:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can trust us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.36,0:07:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna turn our backs on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.19,0:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you really think Leo was the first?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That he didn't say those\Nexact same words to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.90,0:08:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry but you have\Nto understand that my
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.23,0:08:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviors are backed by experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not saying that I have reason
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.48,0:08:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to think you will betray me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.86,0:08:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that I have reasons\Nfor the things that I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The secrets I keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.19,0:08:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.57,0:08:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the relic?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.82,0:08:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It got scattered in the crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.15,0:08:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please, hand it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.90,0:08:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- So all those times\Nyou talked about having
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.86,0:08:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,faith in humanity, that\Nwas just for everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(sighs)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.86,0:08:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's not what I meant to suggest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Rose, the relic is a\Npowerful item and I simply
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.11,0:08:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,feel as though it is my burden to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.36,0:08:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- But you said it couldn't\Ndo anything right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.15,0:09:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Why does it matter who carries it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.40,0:09:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- I need you to listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oz?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.61,0:09:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying to stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.03,0:09:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stop her from what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.44,0:09:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- He's afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.23,0:09:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find out what he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.11,0:09:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.61,0:09:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Jinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Say her name to summon her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.36,0:09:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.61,0:09:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,(wind howling)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.19,0:09:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.65,0:09:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(mystical music)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,(moans)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.36,0:10:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, what knowledge do you seek?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.32,0:10:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(footsteps)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(suspenseful music)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.86,0:10:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-[Newscaster] The perpetrators, Cinder Fall,\NHazel Rainart, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.57,0:11:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have still not been seen since the attack\Nand are presumed to have fled the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.65,0:11:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mistral police department is offering a reward to any citizen...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,(rain and thunder)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.69,0:11:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,(market chatter)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,(foreboding music)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.44,0:11:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(animal screeching)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.11,0:11:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,(footsteps)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,(creaking floorboards)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:11:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,(liens clatter)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.57,0:12:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.11,0:12:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're Lil' Miss Malachite?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.65,0:12:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm Lil' Miss Gon'-Skin-You-Alive
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.61,0:12:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you ever take that tone with me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.19,0:12:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like your life's savings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.40,0:12:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- It was somebody's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.86,0:12:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- (laughs) Cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(electronic beep)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.86,0:12:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Cinder] I'm looking\Nfor these travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.98,0:12:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well sweetheart, you\Ncame to the right place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.07,0:12:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,(gasps)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.57,0:12:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(chuckles) A little jumpy today, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.40,0:12:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I used to be afraid of spiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.98,0:12:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to know what I did about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:12:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- Learn to kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.28,0:13:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh no, the world needs spiders.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.69,0:13:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I just made the spiders work for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.73,0:13:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find your travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.90,0:13:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,(footsteps)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.61,0:13:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Lil' Miss, we already\Nknow where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.98,0:13:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That big guy asked about 'em last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.94,0:13:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- I know we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.28,0:13:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but what we don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.07,0:13:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is who here in Mistral\Nmight be asking about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(clicking)\N(electronic flutter)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.32,0:13:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- I am Jinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.69,0:13:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A being created by the God\Nof Light to aid humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.40,0:13:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in its pursuit of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.57,0:13:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been graced with\Nthe ability to answer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.78,0:14:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,three questions every 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in luck, as I am\Nstill able to answer--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.48,0:14:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.07,0:14:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,-- two questions this era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.86,0:14:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,- (chuckles) It's a pleasure\Nto see you again old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.48,0:14:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ruby, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.03,0:14:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.57,0:14:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.11,0:14:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do whatever you think is right kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jinn?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.65,0:14:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Ozpin hiding from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.65,0:14:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.78,0:14:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-(gasps)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wha-- what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.65,0:15:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Weiss?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yang?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.94,0:15:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Blake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ruby?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.57,0:15:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruby?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.15,0:15:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yang?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.40,0:15:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jinn] Once upon a time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there stood a lonely tower
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.07,0:15:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that sheltered a lonely girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.73,0:15:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Named,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.90,0:15:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem.
